ID   CUT1_TRIHA              Reviewed;         247 AA.
AC   A0A024SC78;
DT   01-JAN-2020, integrated into UniProtKB/Swiss-Prot.
DE   RecName: Full=Cutinase;
OS   Trichoderma harzianum.
OC   Eukaryota; Fungi; Dikarya; Ascomycota; Pezizomycotina; Sordariomycetes;
OC   Hypocreomycetidae; Hypocreales; Hypocreaceae; Trichoderma.
CC   -!- FUNCTION: Catalyzes the hydrolysis of complex carboxylic polyesters found in the cell wall of plants (PubMed:25219509). Degrades cutin, a macromolecule that forms the structure of the plant cuticle (PubMed:25219509).
CC   -!- CATALYTIC ACTIVITY:
CC       Reaction=cutin + H2O = cutin monomers; EC=3.1.1.74;
CC   -!- ACTIVITY REGULATION: Weakly inhibited by n-undecyl phosphonate (C11Y4) (PubMed:25219509). Activity unaffected by paraoxon (PubMed:25219509).
CC   -!- BIOPHYSICOCHEMICAL PROPERTIES:
CC       pH dependence:
CC         Optimum pH is 4-7.;
CC   -!- SUBCELLULAR LOCATION: Secreted.
CC   -!- DOMAIN: In contract to classical cutinases, possesses a lid formed by two N-terminal helices which covers its active site (PubMed:25219509).
CC   -!- PTM: The 2 disulfide bonds play a critical role in holding the catalytic residues in juxta-position.
CC   -!- SIMILARITY: Belongs to the cutinase family.
CC   ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
